import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['count'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Flight Counts')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight counts between origin and destination airports?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    grouped_data = data.groupby('origin')['count'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
    grouped_data.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("Which origin airport has the highest number of flights?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.boxplot(data['count'])
    plt.ylabel('Number of Flights')
    plt.xticks([1], ['Count'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    avg_count = data['count'].mean()
    plt.axhline(avg_count, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_count:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average number of flights between origin and destination airports?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
